mask.description: Unhalted bus cycles of this core while the other core is halted

event.name: LLC_MISSES
event.description: L2 cache demand requests from this core that missed the L2

event.name: LLC_REFS
event.description: L2 cache demand requests from this core

mask.description: STA Loads blocked by a preceding store with unknown address.
STD Loads blocked by a preceding store with unknown data.
OVERLAP_STORE Loads that partially overlap an earlier store, or 4K aliased with a previous store.
L1D Loads blocked by the L1 data cache.
SB_DRAIN_CYCLES Cycles while stores are blocked due to store buffer drain.
ORDER Cycles while store is waiting for a preceding store to be globally observed.
NOOP A store is blocked due to a conflict with an external or internal snoop.

event.name: MISALIGN_MEM_REF
event.description: number of misaligned data memory references

event.name: SSE_PRE_EXEC
event.description: number of SSE pre-fetch/weakly ordered insns retired

mask.description: prefetch T1 and T2 instructions executed.
ANY Memory accesses that missed the DTLB.
MISS_LD DTLB misses due to load operations.
L0_MISS_LD L0 DTLB misses due to load operations.
MISS_ST TLB misses due to store operations.
SUCCESS Number of loads that were successfully disambiguated.
CYCLES Duration of page-walks in core cycles.

event.name: FLOPS
event.description: number of FP computational micro-ops executed

event.description: cycles divider is busy and all other execution units are idle.

mask.description: FP Delayed bypass to FP operation.
